   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX DIVISION DAMAGING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE ONENESS OF THE BODY Scripture Reading: 1 Cor 1:10-13; 3:3-4; 4:6; 11:17, 29-30, 19; 12:24-25; Eph 4:2; Rom 16:17; Titus 3:10; Lev 13:45-46; Num 12:10-15.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>OUTLINE Divisions being among the Corinthians 1 Cor 1:10: All not speaking the same thing.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Not being attuned in the same mind and in the same opinion.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Having, rather, jealousy and strife 1 Cor 1:11; 3:3.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Making parties by saying, I am of Paul, I am of Apollos, I am of Cephas, and I am of Christ 1 Cor 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Such divisions being condemned by the apostle's teaching: Being fleshly and walking according to man 1 Cor 3:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Is Christ divided?</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Was Paul crucified for you?</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Or were you baptized into the name of Paul?</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>1 Cor 1:13.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Being puffed up on behalf of the one, against the other 1 Cor 4:6.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Such divisive ones coming together to take the Lord's table not for the better not for profit but for the worse for loss 1 Cor 11:17: Not discerning the bread as a symbol of the Lord's physical body that needs to be regarded by them.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Not discerning the bread as a symbol of the Lord's mystical Body that requires them to keep the oneness of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Eating judgment to themselves 1 Cor 11:29.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Because of this, many among them being weak and sick, and a number sleeping 1 Cor 11:30.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Parties of division manifesting those in the church life who are approved 1 Cor 11:19.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Having the same care for all the members to avoid division in the Body 1 Cor 12:25.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>No base, no reason, no excuse, no justification, and no vindication for any kind of division.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Always remember: there is no way for the members of the Body of Christ to be legitimately divided in the Body of Christ!</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>All problems can and should be solved through proper and adequate fellowship by praying together sincerely and thoroughly: By seeking the Lord's solution with an open spirit, a pure heart, a lowly mind, and a meek attitude Eph 4:2.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>According to the teaching of the Scriptures properly interpreted, not understood by taking them out of context.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Without self-interest; the entire pursuit being for the Lord's glory and for the benefit of the Lord's recovery.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>No parties or divisions formed for backing in partiality, threatening, and/or challenging others.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Dealing with divisive members: Turning away from division-makers Rom 16:17.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Rejecting factious, sectarian, members Titus 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Practicing the quarantining of the lepers in typology Lev 13:45-46; Num 12:10-15.</S>
   </TEXT>
